claim.claim-text:
A hydrogen fueling method performed by a dispenser, comprising:
gathering initial state values from a hydrogen supply unit of the dispenser and at least one hydrogen tank of a CHSS;
determining a mass flow, a temperature and pressure inside the hydrogen tank, and a state of charge (SOC) using a pre-stored simple thermodynamic model based on the initial state value;
calculating differences between the determined mass flow, temperature, and pressure and pre-stored respective safety thresholds of the determined mass flow, temperature, and pressure; and
discovering and applying an optimal pressure ramp rate of the hydrogen supply unit based on the calculated differences.

The hydrogen fueling method of any one of claims 5 to 9, wherein the pre-stored simple thermodynamic model is executed while performing:
setting a supplied hydrogen pressure of the dispenser;
calculating a mass flow which is a hydrogen flow rate of the data hydrogen moving device;
calculating a stagnation enthalpy of hydrogen flowing into the hydrogen tank;
calculating a temperature inside the hydrogen tank;
calculating a state of charge (SOC) corresponding to a pressure inside the hydrogen tank and a degree at which the hydrogen tank is filled with hydrogen; and
determining a maximum pressure and maximum temperature of the hydrogen tank and a maximum mass flow corresponding to a maximum hydrogen flow rate of the data hydrogen moving device.
